main event: A visual observation of an unidentified object over Nevada, as reported in a Project Blue Book UFO record.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of approximately 17,000 feet.
The object appeared to be round, flat on the bottom and top, and light gray in color.
The object had no wings, tail, or visible propulsion system.
The object's movement was smooth and stabilized, with no apparent motion noise.
The object was tracked by radar and observed by a ground observer at Nellis Air Force Base.
sighted object: a round, flat, light gray object in the sky
witnesses: USAF personnel at Nellis Air Force Base
photographs: no, the report does not mention any photographs
